queen bee identifier: social treatment (0 = solitary, 1 = 5 callow workers added)
whether day 0 is relative to date of 2nd gas (gas) or date of first offspring eclosion (offe)
number of days from day 0 to date of collection. Day 0 is based on RelTreat
calendar date queen pulled as callow from natal colony
total number of eggs in the nest on date of collection. NA value means that eggs were not counted, and the number is unknown
marginal cell length in queen's first forewing (mm); NA value means that the cell was not measured, and the length is unknown
marginal cell length in queen's second forewing (mm); NA value means that the cell was not measured, and the length is unknown
length of terminal oocyte (mm).  first number in column name is ovary (1-2), second number is terminal oocyte (1-4); NA value means the oocyte was not measured, and the length is unknown

resorption status of ovariole (0 = not resorbed, 1 = resorbed). first number in column name is ovary (1-2), second number is ovariole (1-4); NA value means the oocyte was not measured, and the status is unknown
